{
  "$comment": "Test-environment arrangement for the realms mundus. Applied AFTER a sheet deploy/reinstall to bring the 3 realm backends up configured and ready. Each realm runs, in order: (1) set_canister_config_json — runtime test-mode flags + file_registry id + network (the config that used to be baked in at build time); (2) install_codex_from_registry — the realm's codex package; (3) install_extension_from_registry — demo_simulator, which auto-activates from the runtime demo_data flag set in step 1 (so step order matters). The full ~28-extension set per realm is manifest-driven by the installer; this arrangement owns the runtime config and demonstrates the declarative self-install pattern using the realm backend's existing text-in endpoints. Targets are raw canister ids from deployment-descriptors/test-mundus-layered.yml. registry = uq2mu-kaaaa-aaaah-avqcq-cai.",
